The article discusses the forced diversion of a Ryanair flight by Belarus, resulting in the arrest of a Belarusian journalist. It highlights that these actions go against international norms and are part of a wider crackdown on democracy and human rights in Belarus. The United States, along with its partners and allies, plans to hold the regime accountable by taking various measures. They are calling for an international investigation into the incident, the release of political prisoners, and a political dialogue with opposition leaders and civil society groups. The goal is to conduct free and fair presidential elections under OSCE monitoring.